bio:
Man about town. Creative Director. Entrepreneur.
🏡 New York 📍Rio de Janeiro
✉️ patrick@aguynamedpatrick.com
👇 See my city guides & get my newsletter

list.comment: Behind the bar at @bardomineiro, an awesome old-school joint in the Santa Teresa neighborhood. The bar is known for making a killer feijoada—the traditional Brazilian pork and bean stew. They also make a mean caipirinha: that whole lower shelf is filled with various styles and brands of cachaça.
Oops! Missed my connection in Lisbon, so I had to stay for one more night. But there are worse places I could have landed...not mad at one more visit. ✨

The gorgeous bar at Chicago’s preeminent nouveau steakhouse, @swiftandsons. Anchoring a corner in the industrial West Loop—which has exploded with restaurants and hotels in the past few years—this restaurant, designed by @avroko, showcases the quality of design (and food!) happening here.
Austin’s newest hotel/coffee shop/restaurant is the @carpenterhotel and the cutely named @hotlcoffee, all housed in a former union building for the city’s carpenters.

Back in NYC, and I’m scheming and dreaming of a new @SamsungUS Chef Collection kitchen. This sketch by @AlexaHamptonINC was featured this week on @newyorkermag, in a piece where I talked about the things I’ve collected through my travels and how I incorporate them into my life of entertaining at home. Link in bio for the full article. #sponsored
After a delightful trip abroad with friends, I’m headed back home. But I packed a few bottles of wine to keep the travels going... for a few more days, at least. Ciao, Sicily! 🍷✨🍷
Loving the life on these beaches ✨
What I mean when I say “let’s spend the day by the pool.” 🍹👒💦
Last glimpse out my window of @therobeychicago. I’ve had an incredible time making wonderful new friends. Thanks for having me—peace out Chicago!✌🏼

One of my favorite stops in Austin has been @betterhalfbar, an all-day, bar/coffee shop/diner that basically has everything you need—including WiFi and cocktails on tap. This is the “Greens and Grains” from their breakfast menu, and you’d better believe I introduced a biscuit to sop up some of that savory goodness.
This pretty little place, @vestacoffee, has become my home-away-from-home coffee spot in Las Vegas.

Listening to records on my fave headphones, the MW50+ from @masterdynamic. They’re 2-in-1 wireless headphones, so they’re perfect for travel (they saved me on all my recent flights) or just boppin’ around NYC. #ListenYourWay

🚨GIVEAWAY🚨Good morning from chilly Chicago! Today I’m wearing a full @bonobos look (how great is this jacket?!) and I’m giving away a $500 gift card in this week’s newsletter. If you haven’t already, sign up for the newsletter (link in profile), and follow my adventures in more detail every Friday. 📸: @evantsheehan

Look at this charming coffee spot! East Austin’s @fleetcoffeeco is a wedge of a cafe that—like the best spots in the city—features a rotating list of roasters. Pro tip: they have a small menu of @veracruzatx tacos, so you can skip the line elsewhere. They’re also really nice and have free WiFi. What’s not to love? More on my Austin faves in tomorrow’s newsletter—sign up if you haven’t already (link in profile!).

Rio’s Botafogo neighborhood is where you’ll find young, hip residents drinking microbrews and grabbing gourmet burgers. Sort of this city’s Williamsburg, Shoreditch, or Silverlake—on a smaller scale. We stumbled on the most gorgeous farmers market here and couldn’t help but pick up a few goodies for the road.
Night falls on Ipanema.

Woke up in Vegas! Not that you’d know from this room... I’m staying at @thenomadhotel, which just opened on the strip. That means there’s finally a thoughtful, charming oasis in the the middle of all this madness.
Posting up at @sawadacoffee to get a little work done. Debating whether or not to try one of these green “military lattes” that all the kids are drinking here. 🤔

Unpacking all these gorgeous goods from Portugal. I basically couldn’t stop buying beautifully-packaged things—tins of tuna and bacalao, soap, olive oil, toothpaste(!)—that I encountered in Lisbon. Thanks to everyone who gave me suggestions of places to visit (that’s you @rebekahpeppler, @johnphilp3, and @lauramash!). Be sure to visit my website for my own, newly-curated Lisbon city guide.

This photo doesn’t do justice to the moment: high above the beach of Ipanema, @restauranteflordoceu is hidden in a hillside favela. Chef Tobia Messa makes fresh pasta—Brazilian-infused Italian cuisine—while live jazz plays in the corner, an ocean breeze passes through, and diners overlook the Atlantic beaches below. More on stories!

location.location_name: Jardim Botânico do Rio de Janeiro

list.comment: And just like that, I’m wearing coats back in the city after a week at the beach. I don’t think this old trench of mine is quiiiite going to cut it in this cold. 📷: @samortizphotos

Checking out all the classic Austin spots to see which ones make the cut on my AGNP.co city guide. There’s no question that @hotelsanjose, the original @bunkhousehotels property from @thelizlambert is on the list. The hotel was re-opened in 2000 on the site of a 1940’s motor lodge. It set the precedent for many of the boutiques we love that have been opened over the past two decades.
I booked a holiday trip to Rio using points from my #AmexPlatinum. One of the many reasons I use my @AmericanExpress Card all year long...for moments like this. #AmexAmbassador #AmexLife
TBH it’s been raining pretty much nonstop for the last day, so I may not get to swim much in the pool here at the @belmondcopacabanapalace. But it sure is pretty to look at. #belmondpostcards

The guy next to me was trying to have a conversation about his lake house, but honestly I was more interested in what was happening out the window. So I reached across him and took this photo—somewhere over Utah or Colorado—midway between Las Vegas and Chicago.

A quick little cocktail and a bite to eat at Austin’s new @carpentershallatx. The food is seasonal American—with some under-the-radar European influences. At the moment, I’m eating this thing called “Carmelized Onion Pie,” which is basically a pie version of French onion soup. It’s served with the lightest, creamiest, crème fraîche...and I’m in heaven.

When you’re on the road for so long that it’s time to renew reuse recycle. Thankfully I can get beging the vintage vibes at this laundromat. Thanks to the nice lady who works at Bucktown Bubbles for taking my photo. 🧺

Look at this gorgeous view! Woke up this morning at the charming @mamaruisa, a boutique hotel set in an old hillside mansion in Rio de Janeiro. Opened in 2000, the hotel was the first of its kind in the neighborhood of Santa Teresa, and it has since seen a handful of other similar, small hotels in the area follow
I’m spending Thanksgiving week somewhere warm and tropical—Rio! Just landed and I’m settling in for breakfast at Pérgula at the @belmondcopacabanapalace. #BelmondPostcards
